item.title: Y U NO - generator
item.dc:creator: @Andrew_Ferguson The317Guy
item.description:
@Andrew_Ferguson wrote:

[quote=“Ghost in stack, post:11, topic:407831”][quote author=Andrew Ferguson link=topic=509116.msg3693531#msg3693531 date=1312279080]

There already is one?
But thanks

And no one will download a exe, release it open source.

That’s why I said “Idea from this site.” q:
And no one will download an exe on this forum, just because 95% of this community only uses java :I
If you want it open source, I’ll give it open source, but it’s programmed in visual basic so I don’t think you can do anything with it (;
Flaming will probably begin since I said ‘visual basic’ :I

No, no smart person on this site will download an Exe because we all know how easy it is to pack a keylogger with a FUD encryption into anything.
[/quote]
The crypter will not remain FUD if its scan with virustotal.[/quote]
Look stuff up first.

Ok here’s how and FUD (Fully Un-Detectable) crypter works, it takes the virus coding and turns it into a common Encryption that would normally be easy to detect by virus programs. Then it makes its own completely random Encryption coding for itself and locks the key for that Encryption inside the virus itself so it can still run normally. No virus scanning program can detect a FUD Encryption (one in a million chance because its all completely random).

I said all that to just explain how it works and maybe teach some people why you must be weary of exe files for unknown people on the internet, I’m not dissing this program but it would be nice like you stated to release the source files for those members who feel unsafe.
